{{Infobox University |image_name=Instituto Tecnológico de Santo Domingo logo.jpg |image_size=150px |name=Instituto Tecnológico de Santo Domingo |motto=Asume el Reto ([[Spanish language|Spanish]]) |mottoeng=Accept the Challenge |established=October 9, 1972 |type=[[Private university|Private]] |dean= Dr. Rolando Guzmán |city = [[Santo Domingo]] |state= |country=[[Dominican Republic]] |students= |undergrad= |postgrad= |staff= |free_label = |free = |campus=[[Urban area|Urban]] |mascot= |colors= Red, White and Gray {{color box|#FF0000}} {{color box|#FFFFFF}} |athletics= |affiliations = [[Compostela Group of Universities]] |endowment= |website=http://www.intec.edu.do |logo = [[Image:Intec.png]] |}} '''Instituto Tecnológico de Santo Domingo''' —or '''Santo Domingo Institute of Technology''' (also known as '''INTEC'''), is a [[Private university|private]], [[coeducational]], university in [[Santo Domingo]], [[Dominican Republic]]. It was founded on October 9, 1972, by a group of connoted professional and is considered the best institute of technology in the country.<ref name="Ranking">{{cite web |url = http://www.webometrics.info/top50_latinamerica.asp?cont=centralamerica_caribe |title = Latin American Universities' ranking on the Web Top Central America & Caribe |accessdate = 2007-01-20 |author = |date = July 2006 |work = Webometrics |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070119110959/http://www.webometrics.info/top50_latinamerica.asp?cont=centralamerica_caribe |archivedate = 2007-01-19 |df = }}</ref>
==History== The University began with the intention to contribute to the social transformation of the country, the continuous improvement of the quality of life and the preservation of moral and material patrimony. It was incorporated legally as a non-profit organization by means of Presidential Decree no. 2389 on June 15, 1972. Its original academic activities included [[post-graduate]] programs, permanent education, and scientific research. In 1973, the university integrated other fields of study into its curriculum. Its current curricular structure is based on the System, offering academic programs in [[Engineering]], [[Business]] Administration, the [[Humanities]], [[Social Sciences]], and [[Medicine]].
